# üß† Ultimate Advanced Linux Command Cheat Sheet (v2)

A concise yet comprehensive guide for power users, sysadmins, and developers.  
Covers system management, networking, monitoring, scripting, and more.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Session Management & Persistence
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `screen` | Start a detachable terminal session (`screen -S name`) |
| `screen -ls` | List running screen sessions |
| `screen -r <session>` | Reattach to a screen session |
| `tmux` | Modern alternative to `screen` (terminal multiplexer) |
| `tmux new -s name` | Create a new tmux session |
| `tmux attach -t name` | Attach to a tmux session |
| `nohup command & disown` | Run command immune to hangups |
| `setsid command` | Run process in a new session (no controlling terminal) |

---

## üß© Package, System & Kernel Tools
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `apt-cache policy pkg` | Show repository and version info |
| `dpkg -L pkg` | List installed package files |
| `dpkg -S /path/to/file` | Find which package owns a file |
| `rpm -qf /path/to/file` | RPM equivalent of above |
| `lsmod` | List kernel modules |
| `modprobe <module>` | Load kernel module dynamically |
| `modinfo <module>` | Display module information |
| `uname -a` | Kernel version and architecture |
| `lsb_release -a` | Display distribution details |
| `sysctl -a` | View and tune kernel parameters |

---

## üî• Networking, Firewall & Security
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `ip link set eth0 down` | Bring interface down |
| `ip route show` | Display routing table |
| `ss -tulwn` | Show open ports (replacement for `netstat -tuln`) |
| `nmap -sS <ip>` | Stealth scan (root required) |
| `traceroute <host>` | Show network path |
| `mtr <host>` | Real-time traceroute + ping |
| `iptables -L -v -n` | List current firewall rules |
| `iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 22 -j DROP` | Block SSH port (example) |
| `ufw status` / `ufw allow <port>` | Simple firewall configuration |
| `tcpdump -i eth0 port 80` | Capture packets for analysis |
| `curl ifconfig.me` | Show public IP address |
| `netcat -lvp 4444` | Listen for incoming TCP connections |
| `nc <host> <port>` | Simple TCP client |
| `nethogs` | Show per-process network usage |
| `arp -n` | Show ARP table |

---

## üßÆ Process & Performance
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `pidstat -p <pid> 1` | Monitor CPU usage by process |
| `nice -n 10 command` | Run command with lower CPU priority |
| `renice -n 5 -p <pid>` | Adjust priority of running process |
| `ionice -c2 -n7 <cmd>` | Set I/O priority |
| `ps -eo pid,comm,lstart,etime,%mem,%cpu` | Detailed process snapshot |
| `top -H -p <pid>` | Show threads of a process |
| `watch -n 2 "df -h"` | Repeatedly execute a command every 2s |

---

## üíæ Disk, File, and Storage Power Tools
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `lsblk -f` | Display block devices and filesystems |
| `blkid` | Identify block device UUIDs |
| `fdisk -l` / `parted -l` | List partitions |
| `mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1` | Create ext4 filesystem |
| `tune2fs -l /dev/sda1` | Show filesystem parameters |
| `mount -o remount,rw /` | Remount filesystem as read-write |
| `inotifywait -m /path` | Watch for file changes |
| `df -hT` | Disk usage with filesystem type |
| `du -sh * | sort -hr | head -20` | Top 20 largest directories/files |
| `fuser -v /mnt/data` | Show which processes use a mount point |
| `lsof +D /path` | List open files under a directory |

---

## üß† Data Processing & CLI Power Moves
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `awk '/error/{count++} END{print count}' logfile` | Count occurrences |
| `awk '{sum+=$2} END{print sum}' file` | Sum numeric column |
| `sed -n '10,20p' file` | Print specific lines (10‚Äì20) |
| `grep -E "pattern1|pattern2"` | Regex OR search |
| `cut -d: -f1,7 /etc/passwd` | Extract username and shell |
| `paste file1 file2` | Merge lines side-by-side |
| `column -t file.txt` | Align text in columns |
| `sort -t, -k3,3 -n` | Sort CSV by 3rd column numerically |
| `comm file1 file2` | Compare sorted files |
| `diff -u file1 file2` | Unified diff format |
| `hexdump -C file` | View file in hex + ASCII |

---

## üì¶ Archiving & Backups
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `tar -czf backup.tar.gz dir/` | Compress directory |
| `tar -tzf backup.tar.gz` | List contents |
| `gzip -9 file` / `gunzip file.gz` | Compress/uncompress single file |
| `rsync -aAXHv --exclude={"/dev/*","/proc/*"} / /mnt/backup` | System backup (with exclusions) |
| `dd if=/dev/sda of=/dev/sdb bs=64K conv=noerror,sync` | Clone a disk |
| `pv file.iso | dd of=/dev/sdb bs=4M` | Show progress while writing image |

---

## üßæ System Info, Debugging & Audit
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `dmidecode -t system` | Hardware info (BIOS, manufacturer, etc.) |
| `lshw -short` | Summary of hardware |
| `lscpu` | CPU architecture details |
| `lsusb` | USB devices |
| `lspci` | PCI devices |
| `uptime -p` | Pretty system uptime |
| `who -b` | Last system boot time |
| `last -x` | Show reboot and shutdown logs |
| `sar -n DEV 1 5` | Network traffic stats |
| `dmesg | grep -i error` | Filter kernel errors |
| `journalctl -b -1` | Logs from previous boot |

---

## ‚è∞ Automation, Jobs & Scheduling
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `crontab -e` | Edit user cron jobs |
| `crontab -l` | List current cron jobs |
| `systemctl list-timers` | Show active systemd timers |
| `at now + 5 minutes` | Schedule one-time task |
| `anacron` | Run cron jobs that were missed |
| `watch -n 10 command` | Repeat a command periodically |
| `timeout 5 command` | Run command with time limit |

---

## üß± Containers, DevOps, and Virtualization
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `docker ps -a` | List containers |
| `docker exec -it <container> /bin/bash` | Enter running container |
| `docker system prune` | Clean up unused containers/images |
| `podman ps` | Docker alternative (rootless) |
| `vagrant up` / `vagrant ssh` | Launch and connect to VM |
| `ansible -m ping all -i inventory.ini` | Test Ansible connectivity |
| `kubectl get pods -A` | List all Kubernetes pods |
| `virt-manager` | GUI VM management |
| `virsh list --all` | Manage KVM-based VMs |

---

## üß® Miscellaneous Pro Tricks
| Command | Description |
|----------|--------------|
| `history | grep <keyword>` | Search your command history |
| `alias | grep <name>` | Find defined aliases |
| `fc -l` | Show and re-edit command history |
| `export HISTCONTROL=ignoredups` | Ignore duplicates in bash history |
| `time command` | Measure execution time |
| `date -u` | Show UTC time |
| `cal -3` | Show 3-month calendar |
| `rev` | Reverse lines of text |
| `tldr <command>` | Simplified man page summary (install via `pip`) |
| `yes "test" | head -n 5` | Generate repeated output quickly |
| `uuidgen` | Generate random UUIDs |

